47/*
48 * we use the following datastructures in two modes
49 * either in the NTP itself where we use NTP time stamps at some places
50 * or in the kernel, where only struct timeval will be used.
51 */
52#undef PARSEKERNEL
53#if defined(KERNEL) || defined(_KERNEL)
54#ifndef PARSESTREAM
55#define PARSESTREAM
56#endif
57#endif
58#if defined(PARSESTREAM) && defined(HAVE_SYS_STREAM_H)
59#define PARSEKERNEL
60#endif
61#ifdef PARSEKERNEL
62#ifndef _KERNEL
63extern caddr_t kmem_alloc (unsigned int);
64extern caddr_t kmem_free (caddr_t, unsigned int);
65extern unsigned int splx (unsigned int);
66extern unsigned int splhigh (void);
67extern unsigned int splclock (void);
68#define MALLOC(_X_) (char *)kmem_alloc(_X_)
69#define FREE(_X_, _Y_) kmem_free((caddr_t)_X_, _Y_)
70#else
71#include <sys/kmem.h>
72#define MALLOC(_X_) (char *)kmem_alloc(_X_, KM_SLEEP)
73#define FREE(_X_, _Y_) kmem_free((caddr_t)_X_, _Y_)
74#endif
75#else
76#define MALLOC(_X_) malloc(_X_)
77#define FREE(_X_, _Y_) free(_X_)
78#endif

95#if defined(timercmp) && defined(__GNUC__)

99#if !defined(timercmp)
100#define timercmp(tvp, uvp, cmp) \
101 ((tvp)->tv_sec cmp (uvp)->tv_sec || \
102 ((tvp)->tv_sec == (uvp)->tv_sec && (tvp)->tv_usec cmp (uvp)->tv_usec))
103#endif

105#ifndef TIMES10
106#define TIMES10(_X_) (((_X_) << 3) + ((_X_) << 1))
107#endif

109/*
110 * some constants useful for GPS time conversion
111 */
112#define GPSORIGIN 2524953600UL /* NTP origin - GPS origin in seconds */
113#define GPSWRAP 990 /* assume week count less than this in the previous epoch */
114#define GPSWEEKS 1024 /* number of weeks until the GPS epch rolls over */
115
116/*
117 * state flags
118 */
119#define PARSEB_POWERUP 0x00000001 /* no synchronisation */
120#define PARSEB_NOSYNC 0x00000002 /* timecode currently not confirmed */
121
122/*
123 * time zone information
124 */
125#define PARSEB_ANNOUNCE 0x00000010 /* switch time zone warning (DST switch) */
126#define PARSEB_DST 0x00000020 /* DST in effect */
127#define PARSEB_UTC 0x00000040 /* UTC time */
128
129/*
130 * leap information
131 */
132#define PARSEB_LEAPDEL 0x00000100 /* LEAP deletion warning */
133#define PARSEB_LEAPADD 0x00000200 /* LEAP addition warning */
134#define PARSEB_LEAPS 0x00000300 /* LEAP warnings */
135#define PARSEB_LEAPSECOND 0x00000400 /* actual leap second */
136/*
137 * optional status information
138 */
139#define PARSEB_CALLBIT 0x00001000 /* "call bit" used to signalize irregularities in the control facilities */
140#define PARSEB_POSITION 0x00002000 /* position available */
141#define PARSEB_MESSAGE 0x00004000 /* addtitional message data */
142/*
143 * feature information
144 */
145#define PARSEB_S_LEAP 0x00010000 /* supports LEAP */
146#define PARSEB_S_CALLBIT 0x00020000 /* supports callbit information */
147#define PARSEB_S_PPS 0x00040000 /* supports PPS time stamping */
148#define PARSEB_S_POSITION 0x00080000 /* supports position information (GPS) */
149
150/*
151 * time stamp availability
152 */
153#define PARSEB_TIMECODE 0x10000000 /* valid time code sample */
154#define PARSEB_PPS 0x20000000 /* valid PPS sample */
155
156#define PARSE_TCINFO (PARSEB_ANNOUNCE|PARSEB_POWERUP|PARSEB_NOSYNC|PARSEB_DST|\
157 PARSEB_UTC|PARSEB_LEAPS|PARSEB_CALLBIT|PARSEB_S_LEAP|\
158 PARSEB_S_LOCATION|PARSEB_TIMECODE|PARSEB_MESSAGE)
159
160#define PARSE_POWERUP(x) ((x) & PARSEB_POWERUP)
161#define PARSE_NOSYNC(x) (((x) & (PARSEB_POWERUP|PARSEB_NOSYNC)) == PARSEB_NOSYNC)
162#define PARSE_SYNC(x) (((x) & (PARSEB_POWERUP|PARSEB_NOSYNC)) == 0)
163#define PARSE_ANNOUNCE(x) ((x) & PARSEB_ANNOUNCE)
164#define PARSE_DST(x) ((x) & PARSEB_DST)
165#define PARSE_UTC(x) ((x) & PARSEB_UTC)
166#define PARSE_LEAPADD(x) (PARSE_SYNC(x) && (((x) & PARSEB_LEAPS) == PARSEB_LEAPADD))
167#define PARSE_LEAPDEL(x) (PARSE_SYNC(x) && (((x) & PARSEB_LEAPS) == PARSEB_LEAPDEL))
168#define PARSE_CALLBIT(x) ((x) & PARSEB_CALLBIT)
169#define PARSE_LEAPSECOND(x) (PARSE_SYNC(x) && ((x) & PARSEB_LEAP_SECOND))
170
171#define PARSE_S_LEAP(x) ((x) & PARSEB_S_LEAP)
172#define PARSE_S_CALLBIT(x) ((x) & PARSEB_S_CALLBIT)
173#define PARSE_S_PPS(x) ((x) & PARSEB_S_PPS)
174#define PARSE_S_POSITION(x) ((x) & PARSEB_S_POSITION)
175
176#define PARSE_TIMECODE(x) ((x) & PARSEB_TIMECODE)
177#define PARSE_PPS(x) ((x) & PARSEB_PPS)
178#define PARSE_POSITION(x) ((x) & PARSEB_POSITION)
179#define PARSE_MESSAGE(x) ((x) & PARSEB_MESSAGE)
180
181/*
182 * operation flags - lower nibble contains fudge flags
183 */
184#define PARSE_TRUSTTIME CLK_FLAG1 /* use flag1 to indicate the time2 references mean the trust time */
185#define PARSE_CLEAR CLK_FLAG2 /* use flag2 to control pps on assert */
186#define PARSE_PPSKERNEL CLK_FLAG3 /* use flag3 to bind PPS to kernel */
187#define PARSE_LEAP_DELETE CLK_FLAG4 /* use flag4 to force leap deletion - only necessary when earth slows down */
188
189#define PARSE_FIXED_FMT 0x10 /* fixed format */
190#define PARSE_PPSCLOCK 0x20 /* try to get PPS time stamp via ppsclock ioctl */
191
192/*
193 * size of buffers
194 */
195#define PARSE_TCMAX 400 /* maximum addition data size */
196
197typedef union
198{
199 struct timeval tv; /* timeval - kernel view */
200 l_fp fp; /* fixed point - ntp view */
201} timestamp_t;
202
203/*
204 * standard time stamp structure
205 */
206struct parsetime
207{
208 u_long parse_status; /* data status - CVT_OK, CVT_NONE, CVT_FAIL ... */
209 timestamp_t parse_time; /* PARSE timestamp */
210 timestamp_t parse_stime; /* telegram sample timestamp */
211 timestamp_t parse_ptime; /* PPS time stamp */
212 long parse_usecerror; /* sampled usec error */
213 u_long parse_state; /* current receiver state */
214 unsigned short parse_format; /* format code */
215 unsigned short parse_msglen; /* length of message */
216 unsigned char parse_msg[PARSE_TCMAX]; /* original messages */
217};
218
219typedef struct parsetime parsetime_t;
220

222
223#ifdef HAVE_SYS_STREAM_H
224/*
225 * ioctls
226 */
227#define PARSEIOC_ENABLE (('D'<<8) + 'E')
228#define PARSEIOC_DISABLE (('D'<<8) + 'D')
229#define PARSEIOC_SETFMT (('D'<<8) + 'f')
230#define PARSEIOC_GETFMT (('D'<<8) + 'F')
231#define PARSEIOC_SETCS (('D'<<8) + 'C')
232#define PARSEIOC_TIMECODE (('D'<<8) + 'T')
233
234#endif

236/*------ IO handling flags (sorry) ------*/
237
238#define PARSE_IO_CSIZE 0x00000003
239#define PARSE_IO_CS5 0x00000000
240#define PARSE_IO_CS6 0x00000001
241#define PARSE_IO_CS7 0x00000002
242#define PARSE_IO_CS8 0x00000003
243
244/*
245 * ioctl structure
246 */
247union parsectl
248{
249 struct parsegettc
250 {
251 u_long parse_state; /* last state */
252 u_long parse_badformat; /* number of bad packets since last query */
253 unsigned short parse_format;/* last decoded format */
254 unsigned short parse_count; /* count of valid time code bytes */
255 char parse_buffer[PARSE_TCMAX+1]; /* timecode buffer */
256 } parsegettc;
257
258 struct parseformat
259 {
260 unsigned short parse_format;/* number of examined format */
261 unsigned short parse_count; /* count of valid string bytes */
262 char parse_buffer[PARSE_TCMAX+1]; /* format code string */
263 } parseformat;
264
265 struct parsesetcs
266 {
267 u_long parse_cs; /* character size (needed for stripping) */
268 } parsesetcs;
269};
270
271typedef union parsectl parsectl_t;
272
273/*------ for conversion routines --------*/
274
275struct parse /* parse module local data */
276{
277 int parse_flags; /* operation and current status flags */
278
279 int parse_ioflags; /* io handling flags (5-8 Bit control currently) */
280
281 /*
282 * private data - fixed format only
283 */
284 unsigned short parse_plen; /* length of private data */
285 void *parse_pdata; /* private data pointer */
286
287 /*
288 * time code input buffer (from RS232 or PPS)
289 */
290 unsigned short parse_index; /* current buffer index */
291 char *parse_data; /* data buffer */
292 unsigned short parse_dsize; /* size of data buffer */
293 unsigned short parse_lformat; /* last format used */
294 u_long parse_lstate; /* last state code */
295 char *parse_ldata; /* last data buffer */
296 unsigned short parse_ldsize; /* last data buffer length */
297 u_long parse_badformat; /* number of unparsable pakets */
298
299 timestamp_t parse_lastchar; /* last time a character was received */
300 parsetime_t parse_dtime; /* external data prototype */
301};
302
303typedef struct parse parse_t;
304
305struct clocktime /* clock time broken up from time code */
306{
307 long day;
308 long month;
309 long year;
310 long hour;
311 long minute;
312 long second;
313 long usecond;
314 long utcoffset; /* in seconds */
315 time_t utctime; /* the actual time - alternative to date/time */
316 u_long flags; /* current clock status */
317};
318
319typedef struct clocktime clocktime_t;
320
321/*
322 * parser related return/error codes
323 */
324#define CVT_MASK (unsigned)0x0000000F /* conversion exit code */
325#define CVT_NONE (unsigned)0x00000001 /* format not applicable */
326#define CVT_FAIL (unsigned)0x00000002 /* conversion failed - error code returned */
327#define CVT_OK (unsigned)0x00000004 /* conversion succeeded */
328#define CVT_SKIP (unsigned)0x00000008 /* conversion succeeded */
329#define CVT_ADDITIONAL (unsigned)0x00000010 /* additional data is available */
330#define CVT_BADFMT (unsigned)0x00000100 /* general format error - (unparsable) */
331#define CVT_BADDATE (unsigned)0x00000200 /* date field incorrect */
332#define CVT_BADTIME (unsigned)0x00000400 /* time field incorrect */
333
334/*
335 * return codes used by special input parsers
336 */
337#define PARSE_INP_SKIP 0x00 /* discard data - may have been consumed */
338#define PARSE_INP_TIME 0x01 /* time code assembled */
339#define PARSE_INP_PARSE 0x02 /* parse data using normal algorithm */
340#define PARSE_INP_DATA 0x04 /* additional data to pass up */
341#define PARSE_INP_SYNTH 0x08 /* just pass up synthesized time */
342
343/*
344 * PPS edge info
345 */
346#define SYNC_ZERO 0x00
347#define SYNC_ONE 0x01
348
349typedef u_long parse_inp_fnc_t(parse_t *, char, timestamp_t *);
350typedef u_long parse_cvt_fnc_t(unsigned char *, int, struct format *, clocktime_t *, void *);
351typedef u_long parse_pps_fnc_t(parse_t *, int, timestamp_t *);
352
353struct clockformat
354{
355 /* special input protocol - implies fixed format */
356 parse_inp_fnc_t *input;
357 /* conversion routine */
358 parse_cvt_fnc_t *convert;
359 /* routine for handling RS232 sync events (time stamps) */
360 /* PPS input routine */
361 parse_pps_fnc_t *syncpps;
362 /* time code synthesizer */
363
364 void *data; /* local parameters */
365 const char *name; /* clock format name */
366 unsigned short length; /* maximum length of data packet */
367 unsigned short plen; /* length of private data - implies fixed format */
368};
369
370typedef struct clockformat clockformat_t;
371
